g.text: Social media data migration to trust graph
Plugins for ERP, CRM, e-commerce systems
We often think of Intuition as future-facing—but what if its greatest strength was helping us fix and reconnect the past?

So many systems—ERPs, travel booking software, bureaucracies—are outdated, fragmented, or simply not interoperable. What if Intuition could become a semantic bridge, connecting these silos into a live, contextual graph of trust?
Public administrations that don’t need repeated proof,
Logistics networks that resolve trust failures automatically,
Old CRM data becoming meaningful again when plugged into a living reputation layer?
Maybe the real revolution is not replacing the old, but making it trustworthy, meaningful, and alive again.
